A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a retro world map mounted on a wood-paneled office wall, featuring multiple ornate analog clocks positioned at different cities across the globe. Each clock shows a different time, with warm amber desk lamp lighting casting soft shadows. The clocks have brass bezels and roman numerals, connected by elegant curved lines suggesting global connections. Small colored indicator lights glow beside each clock—green, yellow, and red—like vintage radio panel indicators. The color palette features muted browns, creams, teals, and warm oranges typical of mid-century modern design. A steaming coffee cup sits on a mahogany desk in the foreground, slightly out of focus, suggesting early morning international coordination.
